# Performance Rules

## Flutter

Avoid:

- Rebuilding entire screens unnecessarily
- Loading full Firestore collections
- Large uncompressed images
- Blocking UI thread
- Repeated WebView recreation
- Unbounded real-time listeners
- Heavy processing in widget `build()`
- Excessive nested scrolling

Use pagination for large data. Cancel streams when no longer needed.

## Unity WebGL

Prioritize:

- Small build size and controlled memory
- Low allocation; mobile browser compatibility
- Optimized textures and audio
- Limited initial scene load; reduced shader variants
- Efficient object pooling; lightweight bridge messages

## Firebase

Avoid:

- Unindexed queries, hot documents, unbounded arrays
- Excessive real-time listeners, N+1 reads
- Repeated full leaderboard calculations
- Large documents; excessive Function cold-start dependencies

## Expensive operations

Document: reason, expected volume, mitigation, monitoring plan.

## Review checklist

- [ ] Queries indexed where needed
- [ ] Listeners bounded and cancelled
- [ ] WebGL build size considerations noted for Unity changes
